properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 9 at 11:55AM CST until January 9 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTRY MIX OF FREEZING DRIZZLE AND SNOW EXPECTED TODAY...

.Low pressure approaching from the Northern Plains will produce a
mixture of snow, sleet, freezing rain and freezing drizzle across
the region. While snow and ice accumulations are expected to be
relatively light, driving conditions will be hazardous in some
areas. The threat of freezing precipitation will taper off over
central and eastern Wisconsin later this afternoon as road
temperatures warm above freezing.

* WHAT...Light freezing rain and sleet. A light glaze of ice
expected.

* WHERE...Wood, Portage, Waupaca and Waushara Counties.

* WHEN...Until 2 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on icy road conditions. Travel will be hazardous
on untreated roads, bridges, overpasses, on and off ramps, and
roundabouts.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for Wisconsin can be obtained by
calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
